          "text": "✅ **Complete!** Full interactive circuit:\n\n**Components:**\n- **Servo** on Pin 6 → controlled by potentiometer (0°–180°)\n- **Potentiometer** on A0 → reads angle control\n- **5 Colored LEDs** (Red/D9, Yellow/D10, Green/D11, Blue/D12, Purple/D13) with 220Ω resistors\n\n**How it works:**\n1. Turn potentiometer to move servo in real-time\n2. LEDs flash **sequentially** in a rainbow pattern (Red → Yellow → Green → Blue → Purple)\n3. Each LED stays on for 300ms, then the next one lights up\n4. Cycle repeats continuously\n5. Serial monitor shows pot value & servo angle\n\nWatch the colored LEDs dance in sequence! 🌈✨"
